## Session Memory

**Working memory (read this first):** `memory/state.yaml` — auto-compressed rollup of open items, recent context, god nodes (~20 lines).

Index → `memory.md` (last 30 sessions). Detail → `sessions/` (YAML frontmatter). History → `sessions/archive/` (monthly, sessions older than 14 days).

When you finish a turn that changed code, if a session file was created for this chat, append **one line** to `context:` and any `open:` items the **next** agent needs — not prose decisions. Git diff covers *what* changed.

Only add `facts:` bullets when scout flagged HIGH/CRITICAL god nodes.

Manual compress: `python3 .cursor/hooks/compress-memory.py`

Optional SDLC workflow → `.cursor/rules/sdlc.mdc` (invoke for large features, not every chat).
